{
  "texts": [
    "Two RCs are mapped on a fully β sheet fold that binds to three Ca 2+ ions (1 Ca 2+ is enclosed in a loop, 2 Ca 2+ is more solvent exposed and closer to 3 Ca 2+, which is coordinated by an asparagine (N564) and an aspartic acid (D665), Fig. 1b).",
    "Within the community I, most residues (in red sticks) that are identified from EVCs bind to the three Ca 2+ ions, contributing together to stabilize the SdrD fold.",
    "This suggests that EVCs contain the essential information for deducing the functional role of residues, even when they are sparsely distributed across RCs.",
    "Empowered by EVCs and RCs, we implemented the present PhiGnet to assess the functional significance of residues.",
    "We carried out PhiGnet to calculate the activation scores for the functional sites of the mutual gliding-motility (MgIA) protein (annotated with EC 3.6.5.2) (Fig. 1c)."
  ]
}